title: Gerrold_M2_Knocks
tags: mission2 gerrold opening
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Gerrold Pell, the widower — Mission 2 dialogue.
// Author: Inara Vellis (Lead Memory Writer)
// Spec:   Docs/Depth_Bible/Mission_1_2_Focus/02_THE_WIDOWER_GERROLD.md § 7
// Guide:  Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_MISSION_2.md § 8–18
//
// Voice signature (Vellis Rules § 2.1, Focus 02 § 2.1):
//   • Apologises constantly (over-thoughtfully, never weakly).
//   • Talks to the player like a doctor — formal sentence structure.
//   • Verbal tic: "the long bit" (recurs 4 times across the mission).
//   • Never asks for sympathy.
//   • Was a carpenter — craft metaphors when emotion fails him.
//   • Brings the orb in Margery's ironed handkerchief.
//   • Does NOT cry on-screen. The player will.
//
// Variables wired via YarnVillageStateBridge.cs:
//   $met_gerrold, $offered_gerrold_tea, $deferred_gerrold
//   $trust_gerrold (int), $tea_brewed ("Lavender"|"Valerian"|"")
//   $cleanse_quality ("Perfect"|"Acceptable"|"Sloppy"|"CrossedCore")
//   $gerrold_choice ("erase"|"cleanse"|"listen"|"defer")
//   $sat_in_gerrold_chair, $sat_in_margery_chair
//   $vow_1_consent, $vow_3_whole, $vow_7_last_light
//   $cinder (int — Confession Booth currency earnable only via Listen)
//   $pickle_approval, $met_doris
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

<<set $met_gerrold = false>>

// Pickle's pre-knock line plays via Pickle.yarn → Pickle_M2_PreKnock just before this node.

<<eyes_look_at "player">>
Gerrold: I'm sorry. Are you the new keeper?
Gerrold: I should have written first. I don't know if there's a way to do that.
<<wait 0.8>>
Gerrold: ... My name is Gerrold Pell. I — could I come in for a moment?

-> "Yes. Please."
    Gerrold: Thank you. Just for a moment.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_Sits>>
-> "What's this about?"
    Gerrold: ... It's a memory. I brought one.
    Gerrold: I'm sorry — that's what one does, isn't it? I should know how it works.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_Sits>>
-> (Step aside silently and gesture him in)
    Gerrold: Thank you. You are kind.
    <<adjust_vow "vow7" 1>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_Sits>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_Sits
tags: mission2 gerrold sitting
---
<<set $met_gerrold = true>>
<<play_animation "Gerrold" "sit_carefully">>
<<eyes_look_at "handkerchief">>

Gerrold: I'd offer you tea but it's your kettle.
Gerrold: ... I'm sorry. That was a joke. It wasn't a good one.

-> "Would you like tea?"
    Gerrold: Aye, that — no. No, thank you. Not today.
    Gerrold: It's kind of you to ask.
    <<set $offered_gerrold_tea = true>>
    <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 1>>
-> (Sit across from him and wait)
    Gerrold: ... Thank you. For not — for not making me say it quickly.
    <<adjust_vow "vow7" 1>>

<<wait 1.0>>
Gerrold: I have a memory I want to be rid of.
Gerrold: Not the whole thing. Just the long bit.
<<wait 0.5>>
Gerrold: My wife — Margery — died last winter. Eleven months last week.
Gerrold: I have the memory of the last week of her life. It is the heaviest thing I own.
<<wait 1.5>>
Gerrold: I want to keep my wife. I do not want to keep the long bit.

-> "What was the long bit?"
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_AboutTheLongBit>>
-> "Tell me about Margery first."
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_AboutMargery>>
-> (Just nod and wait)
    Gerrold: ... Thank you. I'll get to it.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_OfferOrb>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_AboutTheLongBit
tags: mission2 gerrold long_bit
---
Gerrold: She was ill for fourteen months.
Gerrold: The dying part — the last week — was kind, in its way.
Gerrold: She wasn't in pain by then. She slept a lot.
Gerrold: But I was awake the whole time. Six days awake. Watching.
<<wait 1.0>>
Gerrold: I cannot un-be the man who watched.
Gerrold: But I think I do not need to remember every hour of it.

<<jump Gerrold_M2_OfferOrb>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_AboutMargery
tags: mission2 gerrold margery_aside
---
// The 6-line aside — Focus 02 § 9.3. "The most quoted line in cozy-game
// playtests of Mission 2." Do not edit without an Inara sign-off.

Gerrold: Margery was — quiet. She read more than she spoke.
Gerrold: She worked at the schoolhouse for thirty years.
Gerrold: Helped Lavinia Embry with the small ones who hadn't learned to read yet.
Gerrold: She was Doris the baker's best friend.
Gerrold: They sat in the kitchen on Sundays for — for thirty years. With bread.

<<if $met_doris == true>>
    Gerrold: You met Doris yesterday, didn't you? She'd have given you bread.
    Gerrold: ... Margery would have wanted to know you.
<<endif>>

<<wait 1.2>>
Gerrold: She taught me how to be quiet around someone you love without making it feel like distance.
Gerrold: That is — that is the gift I lost.
Gerrold: I am very loud, now, on my own.

<<jump Gerrold_M2_OfferOrb>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_OfferOrb
tags: mission2 gerrold offer_orb
---
<<show_orb "GER-007" "in_cloth">>

Gerrold: It's in the cloth. Margery wrapped it.
Gerrold: I think she wrapped it for this.
<<wait 1.0>>
Gerrold: I'd like you to look at it.
Gerrold: If you can. If it's the right time.

-> (Pick up the orb)
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_FirstInspection>>
-> "Tell me what's in it first."
    Gerrold: The last week of her life. I described it already. I'm sorry.
    Gerrold: ... If you want to know in particular — the morning she did not wake.
    Gerrold: Doris was in the kitchen. The snow had stopped.
    Gerrold: I want the long bit gone. I want to keep the morning.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_FirstInspection>>
-> "I need to think. Can you come back tomorrow?"
    <<set $deferred_gerrold = true>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_DeferEarly>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_DeferEarly
tags: mission2 gerrold defer_early
---
// Player deferred BEFORE the orb hand-off. Mission 2 ends with the orb
// still wrapped in its cloth, never opened. Equivalent to Path D's outcome.

Gerrold: A day. Aye. That is fair.
Gerrold: I should not have come this morning expecting an answer.
Gerrold: I will leave the cloth here, if you don't mind.
Gerrold: I will come back tomorrow at the same time.
Gerrold: Take care of it for the night. It is — it is what it is.

<<set $gerrold_choice = "defer">>
<<adjust_trust "gerrold" 1>>
<<dialogue_end>>
<<play_cutscene "Dream2_Variant_E_Defer">>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_FirstInspection
tags: mission2 gerrold inspect echo_web_first_activation
---
<<player_picks_up_orb_from_cloth "GER-007">>
<<orb_appears_cracked>>
<<echo_web_activate "DOR-001" "GER-007" "Doris in kitchen on Sunday">>

// Pickle's Echo Web line plays via Pickle.yarn → Pickle_M2_EchoWeb here.

Gerrold: ... What is —
Gerrold: I don't see it. I'm sorry.

-> (Show Gerrold the orb's cracks)
    Gerrold: Aye. I knew it was — uneven. I've not handled it well.
    Gerrold: I've held it too tight, perhaps. I don't know how these are meant to be handled.
    Gerrold: Some things crack in the hands. The wood, the joint — they tell you.
    Gerrold: I should have asked sooner.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_PathChoice>>
-> (Hold the orb silently)
    Gerrold: ... You are looking at it for a long time.
    Gerrold: Take your time. It is — it is the heaviest thing I own.
    <<adjust_vow "vow7" 1>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_PathChoice>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_PathChoice
tags: mission2 gerrold path_choice
---
Gerrold: Do you want to talk it through? Or do you want me to leave you to it?
Gerrold: I would not mind sitting here.
Gerrold: I would not mind walking with you to my house.
Gerrold: I would not mind, also, going home and leaving the cloth.

-> "Let's walk to your cottage. I'd like to see where she lived."
    <<set $walked_to_gerrold_house = true>>
    <<offer_tea_brewing>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_WalkToCottage>>
-> "I'd like to do it here. Stay if you want."
    <<set $worked_at_hollow = true>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_AtHollowChoice>>
-> "Go home. I'll come find you when it's done."
    <<set $worked_alone = true>>
    Gerrold: Aye. I'd — I'd appreciate that. Thank you.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_PreCleanseAlone>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_WalkToCottage
tags: mission2 gerrold walk village_walk_beat
---
// 35m walk down side lane. Gerrold paces at 1.5 m/s. Lumen lantern halos.
// Composer cue: "Margery walking music" (soft fiddle from inn).

Gerrold: It's been a fair autumn. Cold mornings, but bright.
<<wait 2.0>>
Gerrold: Margery liked the autumns best.
Gerrold: She said the trees gave the village manners.
Gerrold: That is the kind of thing she would say. I never knew how to answer her, exactly.
Gerrold: I just smiled. She did not mind.

<<wait 2.5>>
Gerrold: She taught me how to be quiet around someone you love without making it feel like distance.
Gerrold: I am very loud, now, on my own.
Gerrold: I keep wanting to say things that I do not have to say to anyone.
Gerrold: This is — this is part of why I came to the Hollow.
Gerrold: I cannot keep being this loud.

<<wait 2.0>>
Gerrold: Here. This is the door.
Gerrold: Watch the step — the wood gave last winter and I haven't planed it true yet.

<<jump Gerrold_M2_CottageInterior>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_AtHollowChoice
tags: mission2 gerrold at_hollow
---
Gerrold: Aye. I'll sit here.
Gerrold: I won't watch over your shoulder. I — I trust you.

<<jump Gerrold_M2_TheChoice>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_PreCleanseAlone
tags: mission2 gerrold alone
---
Gerrold: I'll wait at home. Come when you can.
Gerrold: There's no hurry.

<<dialogue_end>>
<<jump Gerrold_M2_TheChoice>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_CottageInterior
tags: mission2 gerrold cottage_interior
---
// Heavy Theme Warning Card fires before this node if toggle is enabled.

<<show_heavy_theme_card "Loss of spouse, terminal illness referenced, a man's grief">>

Gerrold: Have a seat. Either chair.

-> (Sit in the left chair — Gerrold's chair)
    <<set $sat_in_gerrold_chair = true>>
    Gerrold: Aye. That's the right one for you.
    Gerrold: I'll take Margery's, today.
    Gerrold: She wouldn't mind. She wouldn't have minded most things.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_TeaModifier>>
-> (Sit in the right chair — Margery's chair)
    <<set $sat_in_margery_chair = true>>
    Gerrold: ...
    Gerrold: ... Aye. That's all right. I should have said which was mine.
    Gerrold: I should — I should say it more, perhaps.
    // Pickle's Margery-chair line plays via Pickle.yarn → Pickle_M2_MargerysChair
    // (only if pickle_approval >= 50).
    <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 1>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_TeaModifier>>
-> (Stand by the fireplace)
    Gerrold: As you like. The fire's still warm — Doris stopped by yesterday and lit it.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_TeaModifier>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_TeaModifier
tags: mission2 gerrold tea_modifier
---
<<if $tea_brewed == "Lavender">>
    Gerrold: ... is that tea?
    Gerrold: ... thank you.
    <<play_animation "Gerrold" "accept_tea">>
    <<wait 1.5>>
    Gerrold: Margery and I had this tea on our last winter together.
    Gerrold: We had it every evening.
    Gerrold: She said it tasted like the inside of a folded sweater.
    Gerrold: I knew what she meant. I still do.
    <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 2>>
<<elseif $tea_brewed == "Valerian">>
    Gerrold: ... is that tea?
    Gerrold: ... thank you.
    <<play_animation "Gerrold" "accept_tea">>
    <<wait 1.5>>
    Gerrold: Aye. This is the one she used to make me when I could not sleep.
    Gerrold: She would put a sprig of it on the pillow when I — when I could not stop thinking.
    Gerrold: I have not had this in eleven months. ... Thank you. You are very kind.
    <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 2>>
<<endif>>

<<wait 1.0>>
Gerrold: Well, then.
Gerrold: I've said what I've come to say.
Gerrold: I'd like to give you the choice.

<<jump Gerrold_M2_TheChoice>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_TheChoice
tags: mission2 gerrold the_choice first_moral_choice
---
<<show_choice_card_with_orb_in_hand>>

// The choice card UI presents four options with one-sentence fiction-voice
// previews per Mission 2 Guide § 14.1. No timer. Pickle's pre-choice
// commentary fires from Pickle.yarn if pickle_approval >= 50.

-> A — Erase the long bit.
    <<set $gerrold_choice = "erase">>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_ChoiceErase>>
-> B — Cleanse with care.
    <<set $gerrold_choice = "cleanse">>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_ChoiceCleanse>>
-> C — Don't take the memory. Sit with him.
    <<set $gerrold_choice = "listen">>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_ChoiceListen>>
-> D — Ask him to come back tomorrow.
    <<set $gerrold_choice = "defer">>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_ChoiceDefer>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_ChoiceErase
tags: mission2 gerrold choice_erase requires_double_confirm
---
// The HEAVIEST option requires a second confirmation. The choice card UI
// presents this as a 1.5-second confirmation pause, then expands the
// preview, then asks again.

Gerrold: ... Aye. The long bit gone.
Gerrold: All of it.
Gerrold: I — I want to be certain that's what I'm asking for.

-> "Yes, all of it. Erase the long bit."
    Gerrold: Aye. Thank you.
    Gerrold: I'll be here.
    <<set_cleanse_profile "Aggressive">>
    <<dialogue_end>>
    <<start_cleanse_minigame "GER-007">>
-> "Wait — let me think a moment more."
    Gerrold: Of course. Take your time.
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_TheChoice>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_ChoiceCleanse
tags: mission2 gerrold choice_cleanse canonical
---
// Path B — the canonical "good Keeper" path. No re-confirmation needed.

Gerrold: Aye.
Gerrold: ... With care, then. Whatever you can do.
Gerrold: I trust you. I — I don't know you, but I trust you.

<<adjust_vow "vow3" 1>>
<<set_cleanse_profile "Careful">>
<<dialogue_end>>
<<start_cleanse_minigame "GER-007">>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_ChoiceListen
tags: mission2 gerrold choice_listen vow7
---
// The Listen path — Vow 7 (Last Light) full activation.

Gerrold: ... I don't —
Gerrold: I don't understand.
Gerrold: You — you don't want to take it?

-> "I want to listen. Tell me about it. Hold it the whole time. I won't take it."
    Gerrold: ...
    Gerrold: ... All right.
    Gerrold: All right. ... All right.
    <<adjust_vow "vow7" 5>>
    <<adjust_cinder 2>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_ListenScene>>
-> (Reach out and gently place his hands around the orb)
    Gerrold: Aye.
    Gerrold: ... Aye.
    <<adjust_vow "vow7" 7>>
    <<adjust_cinder 3>>
    <<jump Gerrold_M2_ListenScene>>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_ListenScene
tags: mission2 gerrold listen_scene cutscene
---
// The 3-minute Listen Cutscene. Gerrold tells Margery's last week aloud
// while the player sits across from him. Per Mission 2 Guide § 17.2.
// Cutscene Engine drives the camera + composer cue M-MD02-D-prelude.

<<play_cutscene "Mission2_ListenScene_FullMonologue">>
<<adjust_trust "gerrold" 6>>
<<dialogue_end>>
<<play_cutscene "Dream2_Variant_D_Listen">>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_ChoiceDefer
tags: mission2 gerrold choice_defer
---
Gerrold: Aye.
Gerrold: A day, then.
Gerrold: I will come back. I will not be impatient.

<<adjust_trust "gerrold" 1>>
<<set $gerrold_returns_day_3 = true>>
<<dialogue_end>>
<<play_cutscene "Dream2_Variant_E_Defer">>

===

title: Gerrold_M2_Outro_Return
tags: mission2 gerrold outro_return handkerchief
---
// Player returns to Gerrold's cottage with the cloth + orb after the
// Cleanse mini-game (or after the Listen scene). Branches on
// $gerrold_choice + $cleanse_quality.

<<if $gerrold_choice == "erase">>
    <<if $cleanse_quality == "Perfect" || $cleanse_quality == "Acceptable">>
        Gerrold: ... Oh.
        Gerrold: ... Aye.
        Gerrold: I can feel that it's lighter.
        Gerrold: I can still see her face. I cannot — I cannot quite see the last week.
        <<wait 1.2>>
        Gerrold: Thank you. I think — I think this is what I asked for.
        Gerrold: I am not certain it is what I needed.
        Gerrold: I will go inside now. I will see what the morning brings.
        <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 5>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow1" -2>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow3" -3>>
    <<else>>
        // Crossed Core during aggressive erase — disaster outcome.
        Gerrold: ... Oh.
        Gerrold: ... I can't —
        Gerrold: I can't see her clearly.
        Gerrold: That wasn't —
        Gerrold: That wasn't —
        <<wait 1.5>>
        Gerrold: It isn't your fault. It is — it is the cloth and the cold and the long winter.
        Gerrold: I will go home. Thank you for trying.
        <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 2>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow1" -3>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow3" -6>>
        <<set $mission6_recovery_arc_seeded = true>>
    <<endif>>
<<elseif $gerrold_choice == "cleanse">>
    <<if $cleanse_quality == "Perfect">>
        Gerrold: ... Aye.
        Gerrold: I can feel it. The blame is out of me.
        Gerrold: The dying is still there. But I can — I can carry it now, I think.
        Gerrold: Margery is — Margery is whole.
        <<wait 1.5>>
        Gerrold: ... Thank you. I do not know what to say.
        Gerrold: I will go in and read for a bit.
        Gerrold: ... Come back when you can. Doris's bread is on Sundays.
        Gerrold: We could — We could perhaps share one.
        <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 4>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow3" 5>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow1" 3>>
    <<elseif $cleanse_quality == "Acceptable" || $cleanse_quality == "Sloppy">>
        Gerrold: ... Aye.
        Gerrold: It is lighter. Not as light as I'd hoped, but —
        Gerrold: I do not think I should be as light as I'd hoped, perhaps.
        Gerrold: Margery is here. I am here.
        Gerrold: The long bit is — it is part of me, still, but it is no longer the only part.
        <<wait 1.0>>
        Gerrold: Thank you. I will see you in the village square next week.
        <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 4>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow3" 3>>
    <<else>>
        // Crossed Core during careful cleanse — minor disaster.
        Gerrold: ... Mmm.
        Gerrold: I cannot quite — I cannot quite see all of her.
        Gerrold: It is — it is not what I asked for. But it is not your fault.
        Gerrold: Thank you for the try.
        <<adjust_trust "gerrold" 3>>
        <<adjust_vow "vow3" -2>>
        <<set $mission6_recovery_arc_seeded = true>>
    <<endif>>
<<elseif $gerrold_choice == "listen">>
    Gerrold: I told you the whole memory.
    Gerrold: I said it aloud for the first time in eleven months.
    Gerrold: I did not know that I would still have it once I'd said it.
    <<wait 1.5>>
    Gerrold: ... I still have it.
    Gerrold: It is — it is still heavy. But it is — it is no longer alone with me.
    Gerrold: Thank you for sitting. That was — that was a kindness I had not known how to ask for.
    Gerrold: Come for tea on Sunday. Doris brings the bread.
<<endif>>

-> (Hand back the handkerchief)
    Gerrold: Aye. Thank you.
    Gerrold: Margery folded that for me. I'd been losing it for weeks.
    <<wait 1.5>>
    Gerrold: ... Take care of yourself, keeper.

<<dialogue_end>>
<<jump Mission02_Outro_Master>>

===

title: Mission02_Outro_Master
tags: mission2 outro master_jump
---
// Empty hub node — exists so all four paths converge to a single
// post-handkerchief outro flow. The Mission02Director consumes this
// transition to advance to the Day 2 Evening Ledger.

<<jump_to_mission2_outro>>

===
